This is currently very WIP.

This repo has the contents of the old drizzle-automation
bzr repo, as well as the contents of the tests/ dir from
the drizzle source tree.

The python code in drizzle/ here is where the job content
from our old CI system was actually defined (thankfully
not directly in Hudson jobs or it would be lost)

The tests/ dir has the perl-driven functional tests
originally from MySQL and then via what became DTR.

The goal here is a repo similar to OpenStack's Tempest.
We'll put the test definitions here, separately, then
use Zuul to run these tests against built drizzle
containers. They currently assume they're running in
the source tree, but what we really want to test is the
built container image anyway, so we should be able to
update that.t

We can leverage the old drizzle-automation code as
initial scaffolding for a set of Zuul jobs. It doesn't
need to stay python, although it could transition into
ansible modules, or just zuul jobs (they aren't so
fancy they need to actually be in Python)

We'll end up with the following 4 interrelated repos
that will all cross-test each other:

  - drizzle
  - drizzle-test
  - libdrizzle
  - drizzle-client
  - dbd-drizzle

sql-bench uses DBD::drizzle, which in turn
uses libdrizzle. libdrizzle is needed by drizzle-client,
and currently also is used as part of the protocol
implementation in the server.
